definition.value: A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having adenine as the nucleobase.
An L-alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of L-2,4-diaminobutyric acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
Dolichol esterified at the terminal hydroxy group.
A member of the class of indoles that is  acetamide substituted by a 1H-indol-3-yl group at position 2. It is an intermediate in the production of plant hormone indole acetic acid (IAA).
